request.description:
Returns all permissions grouped by `group` — feeds the role create / edit form.

Middleware: `permission:roles.view`.

**Response (200):**
```
{
  "data": [
    { "group": "Admins", "permissions": [ {"id":5,"name":"admins.create"}, ... ] },
    { "group": "Roles",  "permissions": [ {"id":1,"name":"roles.create"}, ... ] },
    { "group": "Users",  "permissions": [ {"id":9,"name":"users.view"},  ... ] }
  ]
}
```

Returns the **entire** nested tree for the country, eager-loaded in one request. Each node carries its level / code / name / depth and a recursive `children` array.

Middleware: `auth:sanctum`, `admin`, `permission:locations.view`.

**Use sparingly** — this issues a recursive CTE over every row for the country and grows linearly with the dataset. Prefer **Top-Level Areas** + **Area Children** for cascading dropdowns; use **Country Tree** only when the UI genuinely needs the whole hierarchy at once (e.g. a tree picker).

**Response (200) — India (truncated):**
```
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Country tree fetched.",
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 1, "level": "ZONE", "level_label": "Zone", "code": "WEST",
      "name": "Western Zone", "depth": 1,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": 2, "level": "STATE", "level_label": "State", "code": "MH",
          "name": "Maharashtra", "depth": 2,
          "children": [
            {
              "id": 3, "level": "DISTRICT", "level_label": "District", "code": "PUNE",
              "name": "Pune", "depth": 3,
              "children": [
                { "id": 4, "level": "CITY", "level_label": "City", "code": "PUNE-CITY",
                  "name": "Pune City", "depth": 4, "children": [] }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
